title: Tim Scott highlights opportunity agenda as Black History Month draws to a close
description: Sen. Tim Scott is the longest-serving Black senator in U.S. history, and the first Black chair of a standing Senate committee in his role atop the powerful Senate Banking, Housing and Urban Affairs Committee.
content:
